olive oil
1 packet Button Mushrooms
1 Carrot
2 clove Garlic
1 packet Fusilli
1 packet Plant-Based Mince
1 packet Tomato Paste
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 sachet Vegetable Stock Powder
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet parsley

• Boil the kettle.
• Thinly slice button mushrooms.
• Finely chop carrot and garlic.

• Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water and a generous pinch of salt.
• Cook fusilli in the boiling water, over high heat, until 'al dente', 12 minutes.
• Reserve pasta water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 11/2 cups for 4 people). Drain fusilli, then return to the saucepan.

TIP: 'Al dente' pasta is cooked through but still slightly firm in the centre.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add carrot and mushrooms and cook, tossing, until browned and softened, 8-10 minutes.

• Add plant-based mince and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

• Reduce heat to medium. Add garlic, tomato paste and classic roast seasoning, then cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add vegetable stock powder, the brown sugar and the reserved pasta water, then simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add fusilli and stir to combine. Season with pepper.

• Divide plant-based mince and mushroom fusilli between bowls.
• Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!